Package de.nec.nle.siafu.types

All the Publishable objects are in here.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Publishable
    All of the information managed by the simulation needs to implement this interface, which guarantees that whatever complex data type is used, it can be flattened into a String form and back from it.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BooleanType
    This Publishable encapsulates a boolean primitive and makes it serializable (it can be flattened and blown up again) for use with Siafu.
    EasyTime
    EasyTime is a representation of an hour and a minute.
    FlatData
    An instance of FlatData represents a Publishable object in flattenned form.
    FloatNumber
    This Publishable encapsulates an double primitive and makes it serializable (it can be flattened and blown up again) for use with Siafu.
    IntegerNumber
    This Publishable encapsulates an int primitive and makes it serializable (it can be flattened and blown up again) for use with Siafu.
    Text
    This Publishable encapsulates a String and makes it serializable (it can be flattened and blown up again) for use with Siafu.
    TextList
    A list of Strings.
    TimePeriod
    This class represents a time period, as given by two EasyTime objects.
    TypeUtils
    Collection of utilities to assist in flattening, checking and perform other operations with the Siafu data types.

Package de.nec.nle.siafu.types Description

All the Publishable objects are in here. If you output your simulation as a CSV file, you will want to use these classes to deserialize the information back into Java objects. Note that the package is not complete, since certain classes, like Place, which is Publishable, rather belong to the model package.
